Adam,

You do not need to install from an msi file. You can just use the  
libraries the compiler produces directly. Also, there  is no need for  
Visual Fortran.  I was not aware of Visual C++ Express until now, but  
learly it is a good idea for Cantera to support this compiler.

Dave


